text: Raquel Diaz Caro (born May 13, 1974 in Barcelona) is a track and field athlete from Spain. She has a disability: She is blind and a T11/B1 type athlete. She raced at the 1996 Summer Paralympics. She finished third in the 100 meter T11 race and fourth in 200 meter T11 race.
